data.chText: 充实；使丰富；使饱含（某物）
data.enText: to improve the quality of sth, often by adding sth to it

data.chText: 科学研究丰富了我们的整个生活。
data.enText: The study of science has enriched all our lives.

data.chText: 多数谷类早餐食物都添加了维生素。
data.enText: Most breakfast cereals are enriched with vitamins.
to make sb/sth rich or richer

data.chText: 靠石油收入富裕起来的国家
data.enText: a nation enriched by oil revenues
He used his position to enrich himself.

tr: make better or improve in quality

example: the oil boom enriched a lot of local people

value.def: To enrich something means to improve its quality, usually by adding something to it.

example.ex: An extended family enriches life in many ways...
example.tran: 大家庭在很多方面会使生活更加丰富多彩。

example.ex: It is important to enrich the soil prior to planting.
example.tran: 在种植前给土壤增肥很重要。

value.def: To enrich someone means to increase the amount of money that they have.

example.ex: He will drain, rather than enrich, the country...
example.tran: 他会耗尽而不是增加该国的财富。

example.ex: Those who know how to use the system can enrich themselves at the expense of the very people who work for those companies.
example.tran: 那些懂得如何利用现行体制的人使自己富有起来，而代价是牺牲真正为那些公司工作的人。

value.def: To enrich a nuclear fuel such as uranium means to increase the number of atoms of a particular kind in it, so that it can be used to produce more energy or a greater explosion.

example.ex: It was actually used for enriching uranium to weapons-grade levels.
example.tran: 实际上，它是用来将铀浓缩以制造武器。
